title: fanoutqa: Who are Singapore's most recent five deputy prime ministers (chronological order), and which university did they each attend? (fa599c99bdc4ca27)

chat_history.content: Who are Singapore's most recent five deputy prime ministers (chronological order), and which university did they each attend?

Here are the five most recent Deputy Prime Ministers of Singapore, along with the universities they attended:

1. Lawrence Wong (2022 - present):
    - University of Michigan (Economics and Computer Science)
    - Kennedy School of Government, Harvard University (Public Administration)

2. Heng Swee Keat (2019 - 2022):
    - University of Singapore (Economics)
    - Kennedy School of Government, Harvard University (Master in Public Administration)

3. Teo Chee Hean (2009 - 2019):
    - University of Manchester (Engineering)
    - Kennedy School of Government, Harvard University (Master in Public Administration)

4. Tharman Shanmugaratnam (2007 - 2019):
    - London School of Economics (Economics)
    - Kennedy School of Government, Harvard University (Master in Public Administration)

5. Tony Tan (1995 - 2005):
    - University of Adelaide (Engineering)
    - Massachusetts Institute of Technology (Doctorate in Applied Mathematics)
